<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="72" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="5" pageNumber="72">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="5" pageNumber="72">
The species was fully described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Londt, JGH" journalOrPublisher="Journal of the Entomological Society of Southern Africa" pageId="13" pageNumber="80" pagination="1 - 6" title="Gibbasilusarenaceus, a new genus and species from the western Cape Province of South Africa (Diptera: Asilidae: Asilinae)." volume="49" year="1986">Londt (1986)</bibRefCitation>
who provided illustrations of the general habitus, antenna, wing, ♂ terminalia, ♀ ovipositor and pupa as indicated above. The species bears a strong resemblance to the newly described 
<taxonomicName lsidName="crinitus" pageId="5" pageNumber="72" rank="species" species="crinitus">crinitus</taxonomicName>
sp. n. (see below). A new illustration of the ♀ ovipositor is here provided for comparative purposes (Fig. 7). The length: depth ratio of the ovipositor = 4.0: 1.
</paragraph>
